data.name: Gulfstream IV Summer Night Fishing
data.desc:
Summer Night Fishing 7-12:30
Fishing Key West at night has a lot of advantages. The most obvious advantage is that you’re not fishing in the sun. No need for sunscreen and sunglasses on this trip. The ocean is calm, the weather is beautiful and cool. It’s really relaxing to fish at nighttime. You've got the whole ocean to yourself. Unlike the day, which can be crowded with dozens of other fishermen fishing the same areas as you, the ocean at night is relatively unoccupied by other fishing vessels. 
 
There are quite a few fish that bite better during the night. Snappers, sharks, barracuda and a dozen other species bite so much better during the night time than they do during the day. A Key West favorite is the Mangrove Snapper. Snapper fishing offers a lot more action at night than during the day. Also snapper is one of the best eating fish in the ocean
data.excerpt: June 15-August 31 Friday and Sat nights. When the mangrove snapper spawn begins, we add trips 7 days a week. Those dates are dependent upon the fish.

data.name: Private Charter for 25-45 People
data.desc:
For fishing, the Gulfstream IV accommodates up to 45 adult passengers. With over 35 years of experience catering to party cruises, dinner cruises, and charter fishing , we are experts at designing  your cruise or charter to ensure a unique and memorable nautical experience. If you’re looking for a one of a kind fishing experience, the Gulfstream IV will give you a thrill of a lifetime.
Our unique combination of  experienced and professional crew  provides our clients with a unique venue to host your next function while enjoying Key West’s nautical seascapes.
Sailing from Key West’s Historic Charter Boat Row, our vessel offers the latest in modern amenities and comforts for family, friends and/or corporate charters. We offer a beautifully appointed fishing vessel – with plenty of room to enjoy magnificent views, scenic waterways and spectacular sunsets on Key West’s beautiful Atlantic/Gulf line. Our vessel is equipped with a sound system, onboard galley and a courteous and efficient crew – all to ensure the success of your charter event. Add to this our spacious walk-around decks and a fully enclosed cabin – Our Vessels are ideal for your next special event.

data.name: Gulfstream IV Party Boat Fishing Trip
data.desc:
Our Key West Party Boat Fishing Charter is the longest running deep sea fishing charter in Key West, Florida, catching payloads of fish since 1947.

Led by a professionally trained and licensed crew, your fishing adventure aboard Gulfstream IV includes fishing tackle, license, bait, ice and even a few choice secrets locals have used to catch record breaking snapper, cobia, amberjack, grouper and more. The mates will be happy to bait your hook, remove fish from your line and put them on ice, unless, you wish to release them. And upon return, they will clean, filet and bag your fish for you (.50 per fish)
data.excerpt: We have the longest head boat trip in the Key West  for the same prices as some of the shorter trips. Bottom fishing for snapper, grouper, mackerel and shark.

data.name: 10,000 Island and Marco Island Seaplane Tour
data.desc: The tour begins from Marco Island Executive Airport and heads south towards Goodland, Everglade City. Once airborne the marine environment presents the coastal barrier islands, the in-sound islands, mangroves and estuaries of this very healthy marine eco-system. The many channels between the Gulf of Mexico and Islands present unique aerial viewing and photographic opportunities to see marine mammals, sharks and large ray – all easily visible from the comfort of your seaplane.

data.name: Wild and Scenic Loxahatchee River Tour
data.desc: This Eco-Tour is a great way to get a feel for how Florida looked centuries ago, and gives you a chance to explore the waterways and wildlife of the upper section of the Wild and Scenic Loxahatchee River.
